:::summary
European history is the story of Western civilization — the extraordinary tradition born in ancient Greece and Rome, transformed by Christianity, refined through medieval Christendom, exploded by the Renaissance and Reformation, tested by the Enlightenment and the wars of ideology, and carrying into the present an inheritance of philosophy, law, science, art, and faith without parallel in human history. To understand Europe is to understand the roots of the world we inhabit.
:::

